    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/org/computational-fluid-dynamics-lab",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. Validation evidence demonstrates CFD model predicts relative hemolysis index within acceptable tolerance across all 5 operating points. A screening sensitivity exercise during model development confirmed that impeller tip clearance and volute geometry are dominant parameters; this informed factor ratings and boundary condition selection. The model is judged credible for its intended use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device submission.",
